text.section:
Except as provided in subsection (c) of this section, a law enforcement agency seeking to dispose of a handgun owned by the agency shall:
destroy the handgun;
sell, exchange, or transfer the handgun to another law enforcement agency for official use by that agency;
sell the handgun to a retired police employee in accordance with § 2-415(c) of this article;
sell the handgun to the law enforcement officer to whom the handgun was assigned; or
sell, exchange, or transfer the handgun to a manufacturer.
